OMNI WIKI TOOL - DOCUMENTATION
==============================

ABOUT
-----
Omni `wiki` is a static site generator and management tool built into the Omni Shell Framework. It converts Markdown files into linked HTML sites with built-in support for custom blocks, diagrams, and cross-referencing.

CLI COMMANDS
------------
Usage: `wiki <command> [args]`
* ls            : List registered wikis.
* new/set       : Create/update a wiki (`wiki new <name> -p <path>`). Options: `-c` (content), `-d` (dist), `-t` (templates), `-s` (static).
* rm            : Remove a wiki configuration.
* pages         : Manage pages (`ls`, `new/set -p <path>`, `rm -p <slug>`).
* template      : Manage layouts (`ls`, `new/set -p <path>`, `rm`).
* topic / ref   : Manage cross-page references (`wiki ref new/set <ref> -w <wiki> -e <env> -t <topic> -v <value>`).
* block         : Manage custom div blocks (`wiki block new <name> -c <css_class>`).
* build         : Compile wiki to HTML (`wiki build <wiki>`). Use `--rebuild` to force full compile.
* serve         : Start a local HTTP server (`wiki serve <wiki> -p <port>`).

PAGE CONFIGURATION (FRONTMATTER)
--------------------------------
Pages support YAML-style frontmatter enclosed in `---`.
* `title`: Sets the display name of the page.
* `weight`: Controls sorting order in the sidebar and featured menus. Smaller numbers appear first (default is 9999 for unweighted pages).

MARKDOWN & INLINE FORMATTING
----------------------------
* Links: `[Text](file.md)` automatically converts `.md` extensions to `.html`.
* Bold: `**text**` or `__text__`
* Italic: `_text_`
* Insert/Underline: `++text++`
* Code: `` `code` ``

ANCHORS & CROSS-REFERENCES
--------------------------
* Create Anchor : `{{#marker_name}}`
* Link to Anchor: `{{=marker_name}}`
* Topic Link    : `{{:topic:label}}` (Resolves to the URL/anchor defined via `wiki ref`).

SPECIAL PLACEHOLDERS
--------------------
Place these exactly as shown on their own lines:
* `{{ toc }}`   : Renders a Table of Contents based on heading levels (`#` to `######`).
* `{{ files }}` : Renders a list of links to sibling files in the current directory.

CUSTOM BLOCKS
-------------
Wrap content in triple backticks and curly braces: ```{{ block_name }} ... ```
1. Built-in `table`: Renders ASCII tables to HTML.
2. Built-in `diagram`: Renders custom SVG diagrams from textual node/arrow definitions.
3. Built-in `def`: Structured definition block.
   Syntax:
   :: name: <term>
   :: context: <category>
   :: def: <definition text>
   :: related: <related links>
   (Automatically generates a reference anchor: `{{:def:context.name}}`).
4. Custom Blocks: User-defined via `wiki block new <name> -c <class>`, wraps content in `<div class="class">...</div>`.

LAYOUTS & TEMPLATING
--------------------
HTML layouts support Jinja-like placeholders replaced during `wiki build`:
* `{{ body }}`       : The parsed Markdown content.
* `{{ pagename }}`   : The page title.
* `{{ menu }}`       : The auto-generated sidebar tree (sorted by weight).
* `{{ featured }}`   : The top-level featured pages menu.
* `{{ page.<key> }}` : Any custom key defined in the page's frontmatter.
* `{{ year }}` / `{{ now }}`: Current year / build timestamp.
